(133, 'Director and Senior Consultant', 'Provided technical M&E leadership to the firm, responsible for leading proposal development, offering M&E training to clients, and leading research on different baselines, evaluations, and assessments.', 'Led implementation of different researches, assessments, surveys, baselines, evaluations and impact assessments. Disseminated different research products to various audiences. Designed appropriate research methodologies. Led writing of various research reports. Applied and obtained ethical approvals for researches.', 4, 70),
(134, 'Regional Planning Monitoring and Reporting Lead', 'Provided strategic-level information for Senior Management decision making and offered technical support in Learning, Appraisal, Monitoring and Evaluation, Impact evaluations, online database management, and data analysis and interpretation.', 'Led design of research and development of M&E systems for all countries. Led M&E training for staff. Provided leadership for East Africa planning annually and led specific program/project reviews. Successfully led development of annual plans and reports. Introduced learning as part of monitoring. Developed a learning strategy.', 4, 71),
(135, 'Senior Programme National Coordinator - Monitoring and Evaluation', 'Provided leadership in the development and implementation of research, planning, monitoring, and evaluation systems for WaterAid Uganda\'s $16 million programs portfolio.', 'Developed national School WASH Indicators. Provided technical support for WAU\'s web-based information system. Managed collection, analysis, and interpretation of field data and report preparation. Designed and implemented periodic field studies. Compiled major reports, case studies, and M&E lessons. Supported development of local learning systems.', 4, 72),
(136, 'National Programme Coordinator - Monitoring and Evaluation', 'Developed WAU M&E guidelines, frameworks, and beneficiary counting protocol. Analyzed gaps in partner M&E systems and designed and facilitated tailor-made training for over 121 partner staff.', 'Conducted numerous evaluations, surveys, and studies for WASH-focused projects with WAU partners, including baselines for malaria and urban WASH projects, evaluations of Kampala urban slums, evaluation of livelihood support, with Hope for Humanity, evaluation of HIV/AIDS project with Pentecostal Assemblies of God, community rural WASH projects and school mapping. Developed project Indicator Tracking tables and data collection tools for 11 projects. Initiated the use of a web-based database.', 4, 73),
(137, 'Monitoring and Evaluation Manager', 'Initiated and completed the establishment of a Country M&E System for LWF Uganda/South Sudan. Coordinated monitoring, evaluation, and reporting for the five regional programs.', 'Directed M&E for WASH programs, including the USAID Multi-Year Assistance Program (MYAP). Identified M&E capacity building needs and trained 179 LWF staff in M&E. Headed planning for the LWF Uganda/South Sudan program. Compiled periodic monitoring reports. Led preparation of project planning documents. Designed and implemented baseline exercises for five new projects. Led seven project evaluations. Ensured regular updating of a three-center database.', 4, 74),
(138, 'Project Officer - Monitoring and Evaluation', 'Led M&E planning of field program activities and participated in the development of LWF Uganda\'s strategic plan. Coordinated preparation and review of the annual planning and monitoring plan for the Statement of Needs (SON) project, and monitored budget and cost of M&E activities.', 'Spearheaded the development and implementation of an impact M&E plan. Trained 48 members of the project staff in M&E. Assisted the Project Manager in the development and review of M&E guidelines. Conducted field research and collected data for statistical analysis of project operations. Facilitated assessment of project impact on beneficiaries and recommended appropriate action.', 4, 75),
(139, 'Project Officer - Emergency', 'Planned, designed, and coordinated the implementation of all community-based activities per the annual budget of $390,000. Supervised 36 Project Assistants and over 70 volunteers and visited project sites regularly.', 'Coordinated emergency relief activities with relevant stakeholders, including the UN, during emergencies including internal displacement caused by armed conflict with Lord Resistance Army and disease outbreaks in internally displaced people\'s camps.', 4, 76),
(140, 'Project Assistant', 'Identified beneficiaries for non-food items and food relief, and mobilized communities for distribution, sanitation meetings, and fencing of water sources.', 'Trained 422 local community leaders and water source management committees in operation and maintenance, sanitation promotion, basic finance management, and participatory monitoring.', 4, 77),
(141, 'Team Lead; Data Collection and Quality Assurance', 'Co-led a comprehensive mapping of Community Health Workers (CHWs) across Mainland Tanzania, documenting their number, distribution, roles, training, and skills while assessing their eligibility for an integrated CHW program.', 'Documented CHW number, distribution, roles, training, skills; assessed eligibility for integrated CHW program; covered all 26 regions and 164 district councils; collected data from approximately 14,518 villages and mitaa.', 5, 78),
(142, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led a comprehensive mapping of non-governmental organizations (NGOs) working on land rights and natural resources conservation across mainland Tanzania.', 'Conducted comprehensive mapping of NGOs; created database of organizations; documented geographical distribution; understood successes and challenges; identified 47 NGOs across 12 regions.', 5, 79),
(143, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led CSO capacity assessments and mapping exercises to strengthen civil society\'s engagement and program effectiveness, focusing on youth-focused organizations in five coastal regions.', 'Identified and assessed youth-focused organizations; analyzed strengths, gaps, potential for collaboration; provided critical insights to enhance program coordination, inform policy decisions, and drive more effective youth-centered interventions.', 5, 80),
(144, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led a barriers and facilitators analysis study to inform program enhancements for the CONNECT Project, focusing on improving support and services for young parents (adolescent girl parents) to access comprehensive healthcare during pregnancy and postpartum.', 'Developed vignette tools; engaged with first-time adolescent girl parents; gathered valuable insights; identified common touchpoints; analyzed factors influencing ANC/delivery/postnatal/PPFP use; assessed health system responses.', 5, 81),
(145, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led a Mid-line Survey for the Niambie 2 Project, utilizing the Human-Centered Design (HCD) approach to benchmark the project\'s outcomes.', 'Assessed media content accessed and consumed; evaluated audience\'s engagement with programmatic content; assessed knowledge and understanding of rights and benefits of young women and girls; evaluated ability of young male and female audiences to discuss and support gender equality, challenge gender-discriminatory norms, and access gender-sensitive services.', 5, 82),
(146, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led baseline, midline and end-line studies to generate information to be used to set and assess project targets and refine performance indicators for malaria prevention, health seeking/diagnosis and treatment.', 'Gauge current knowledge, attitudes and practices (KAP) among project\'s beneficiaries; determine KAP among ANC health care workers; identify barriers towards malaria prevention, testing and treatment among beneficiaries.', 5, 83),
(147, 'Principal Investigator and Team Lead', 'Led the implementation of a Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation (BMGF) funded immunization project, employing Human Centered Design (HCD) approach to identify social norms that prevent completion of childhood immunization.', 'Implemented community-championed social norms marketing approach; built a male engagement solution (Ngosha Jishosha) to increase childhood immunization uptake and reduce vaccine drop-out; increased clients for childhood immunization from 3,750 to 5,874.', 5, 84),
(148, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led management of a 3-month long data collection assignment for the FHI\'s Annual Sentinel to assess the impact of implemented SBC campaigns on the project\'s priority behaviors and behavioral determinants.', 'Led data collection and processing support; developed protocol, data collection tools and field manual; coordinated application for IRB and POLARG approvals; trained 43 Research field team and supervisors; generated clean data set and field report.', 5, 85),
(149, 'Principal Investigator and Team Lead', 'Led DAMAX team to undertake a 17-month data collection assignment for the Beyond Bias project, funded by the Gates Foundation, primarily addressing provider biases and behaviors that hinder youth access to contraceptive services in Dar es Salaam.', 'Utilized Human-Centered Design (HCD) approach; recruited, trained, and managed 50 data enumerators; assumed responsibility for data processing and ensuring data quality assurance; achieved accurate and meaningful insights into the barriers faced by youth in accessing contraceptive services.', 5, 86),
(150, 'Principal Investigator and Team Lead', 'Led DAMAX to support PCI in conducting a baseline and endline assessment for the Early Child Learning and Development Project Consultant Services, which utilized a Human-Centered Design (HCD) intervention.', 'Focused on creating Education Cascade Groups (ECGs) and educational tools to empower young parents in enhancing their parenting skills; obtained accurate and insightful data; formulated targeted interventions to address educational barriers for children and improve education outcomes.', 5, 87),
(151, 'Principal Investigator and Team Lead', 'Led DAMAX to undertake an assessment on retention of Human Resource for Health (HRH) across 15 District of Tanzania for Benjamin Mkapa Foundation (BMF).', 'Employed both quantitative and qualitative methods to collect data on retention mechanism for selected health cadres; visited eight hospitals, 32 health centers and 43 dispensaries; interviewed 417 health workers and 87 district officials; captured a comprehensive picture of the HRH retention landscape.', 5, 88),
(152, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led the design, implementation and reporting for the final evaluation of the KMC project.', 'Assessed changes from baseline on outcome and output indicators; assessed the project against OECD criteria: Relevance, Efficiency, Effectiveness, Gender Sensitivity, Sustainability and Impact; documented lessons learned and best practices.', 5, 89),
(153, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led management of data collection, analysis and reporting for this household survey to assess the effectiveness of savings groups on improving household, caregiver and child well-being.', 'Sampled 750 households in five zones; used cluster sampling; randomly selected thirty clusters (wards) and 25 households from within each cluster (ward).', 5, 90),
(154, 'Lead Consultant', 'Led the design, training of RAs, supervising of data collection, data analysis, documentation & report writing for a cRCT.', 'Measured outcomes through community surveys, routine data, qualitative assessment, and economic evaluation; reached a sample size of 1120 women.', 5, 91),
(155, 'Lead Consultant', 'Led the design, training of RAs, supervising of data collection, data analysis, documentation & report writing.', 'Improved understanding of private sector demand for antimalarial bed nets; estimated households\' willingness-to-pay for various bed net types and attributes; employed a non-hypothetical Discrete Choice Experiment (DCE).', 5, 92),
(156, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led the design, implementation and reporting for a baseline survey of maternal nutrition, birth and post-natal package, and weekly iron and folic acid projects.', 'Enrolled 1,274 mothers of infants, 252 adolescent girls, 115 health providers and 25 schools providing WIFA for girls.', 5, 93),
(157, 'Lead Consultant', 'Led management of data collection, analysis and reporting for this household survey to routinely monitor exposure to Tupange Pamoja programming interventions and modern contraceptive prevalence rate (mCPR).', 'Involved a sample size of 3,186 women and girls of reproductive age and 75 health facilities in all five Municipal Councils of Dar es Salaam Region.', 5, 94),
(158, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led end line evaluation of the project to assess changes brought about by implementing the safe motherhood and fistula project.', 'Involved more than 10 focus group discussion and five Focus Group discussions (FGD) with service providers, fistula clients, regional/district health management teams and project staff.', 5, 95),
(159, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led development of study protocol, submission for IRB approval, training of research assistants, supervise data collection, analysis and report writing.', 'Identified and documented gaps or bottlenecks in the operation of the nutrition-specific supply chain system and proposed needed solutions to address them; conducted 46 in-depth Interviews (IDIs) and 5 Focus group discussion (FGDs).', 5, 96),
(160, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led the preparation of evaluation protocol and tools and application to NIMR for ethical approval. Recruited and trained Research Assistants comprised of medical doctors, nurses, pharmacists, sociologists, gender specialists and statisticians.', 'Led data analysis, transcription and translation and report writing; sampled 2,000 households for structured interviews, conducted 11 FGDs and 14 IDIs; conducted a health facility assessment.', 5, 97),
(161, 'Lead Consultant', 'Led the design, implementation and reporting for this survey to capture baseline information on WORTH group members.', 'Interviewed 383 Adolescent Girls and Young Women (AGYW) and 314 Sex Worker (FSW) from group members in Shinyanga Mbeya, Dar es Salaam, Njombe and Iringa regions of Tanzania.', 5, 98),
(162, 'Principal Investigator', 'Led the design, implementation and reporting for this final project evaluation.', 'Interviewed 440 students; conducted 12 focus group discussions, and 12 in depth interviews for teachers and volunteers.', 5, 99),
(163, 'Principal Investigator', 'Provided overall leadership on development of protocol, IRB application, training of research assistant, field work supervision, quality assurance and data management.', 'Interviewed more than 1,900 women and men using questionnaire; conducted 20 FDGs and 30 IDIs.', 5, 100),
(164, 'Lead Consultant', 'Led the final evaluation for Making Markets Work for Women and Bright Solar Lamps Initiative.', 'Conducted semi-structured interview of more than 100 key informants and 10 focus group discussion with Women groups.', 5, 101),
(165, 'Consultant', 'Consultant in a collaboration work with CDC on the project.', 'Evaluated national ART outcomes and costs of comprehensive HIV treatment at out-patient clinics.', 5, 102),
(166, 'Consultant', 'Consultant in collaboration with Mkapa HIV/AIDS foundation to develop a resource allocation formula for the districts benefiting from the Mkapa fellows programme.', 'Developed resource allocation formula.', 5, 103),
(167, 'Consultant', 'Consultant in collaboration with Columbia University, (AMDD), on the project costing on human resource needed for reducing maternal mortality in Tanzania.', 'Conducted project costing on human resource needed for reducing maternal mortality.', 5, 104),
(168, 'Researcher', 'Evaluated diagnostic cost effectiveness of rapid dipstick tests for malaria diagnosis in improving rational use of antimalarial drugs in Tanzania.', 'Conducted research on diagnostic cost effectiveness.', 5, 105),
(169, 'Researcher', 'Explored the cost of laboratory testing for HIV and major sources of funding for Tanzania.', 'Conducted research on laboratory testing costs and funding sources.', 5, 106),
(170, 'Researcher', 'Researched improving access to medicine in developing Countries, applying New Institution Economics on manufacturing and distribution issues.', 'Conducted research on access to medicine and applied institutional economics.', 5, 107),
(171, 'Assistant Coordinator', 'Assistant coordinator in collaboration with National Tuberculosis and Leprosy Program (NTLP) on the research project: Prevalence of Tuberculosis Survey in Tanzania (PST).', 'Coordinated collaboration on the research project.', 5, 108),
(172, 'Coordinator', 'Coordinated in collaboration with Clinton Foundation: CHAI-CSHOR-NIMR project based on operation research in the scaling up of ARV in resource limited settings.', 'Coordinated operation research in scaling up ARV.', 5, 109),
(173, 'Consultant', 'Consultant for stakeholders analysis and assessment of how health and nutrition research findings feed up into policy development processes within the Ministry of Health of Uganda.', 'Conducted stakeholders analysis and assessment.', 5, 110),
(174, 'Consultant', 'Consultant for assessment of the Availability of Health Services of the Required Mix at Various Levels of the Health System to Ensure Accessibility and Quality of Health Care including the Change of Burden of Diseases Resulting from Climate Changes and Environment.', 'Assessed availability and quality of health services and burden of diseases related to climate change and environment.', 5, 111),
(175, 'Researcher', 'Researched rapid assessment of HIV situation in prisons settings in Mainland Tanzania.', 'Conducted rapid assessment.', 5, 112),
(176, 'Researcher', 'Researched impact of couple-based counseling among HIV sero-discordant individuals and their contribution towards averting HIV transmission in selected districts of Tanzania.', 'Conducted impact research.', 5, 113),
(177, 'Consultant', 'Consultancy with CDC-USA to develop a National Guideline for HIV Counseling and Testing for Revolutionary Government of Zanzibar Ministry of Health and Social Welfare.', 'Developed National Guideline for HIV Counseling and Testing.', 5, 114),
(178, 'Advocacy Fellow', 'Identified and coordinated key windows for consortium members to take effective, joint action to advocate for the right to public education.', 'Developed monitoring and communications products to keep stakeholders abreast of policy developments regarding the Abidjan Principles. Coordinated a high-level dialogue on the challenges to public education with mandate-holders, academics, and civil society leaders.', 6, 115),
(179, 'Communications Manager', 'Managed multi-media awareness and fundraising campaigns from conception to publication.', 'Planned and tracked communications strategies, led media skills capacity-building for field staff, supervised creative contractors, and oversaw project budgets. Composed quarterly advocacy newsletters, bi-weekly appeals, and grant reports.', 6, 116),
(180, 'Research Analyst & Communications Consultant', 'Analysed policies and qualitative data for monitoring, evaluation, and learning reports on education development projects in the Middle East and East Africa.', 'Transformed technical reports into engaging and accessible products for policymakers and practitioners.', 6, 117);
INSERT INTO `profiles_consultantrole` (`id`, `role_title`, `role_description`, `tasks`, `consultant_id`, `project_id`) VALUES
(181, 'Communications Manager / Programmes Associate', 'Identified advocacy opportunities and produced materials on behalf of Nobel Peace Prize Laureate Nadia Murad. Represented the organisation in high-level meetings and correspondence with officials at the UN, US State Department, French Embassy to the US, and other world leaders.', 'Developed policies and training materials on gender equity, protection from sexual exploitation and abuse, and security. Streamlined operations by creating project mapping tools, community outreach material, and daily programmes support for field staff in Sinjar, Iraq.', 6, 118),
(182, 'Strategic Development Intern / Programmes Intern', 'Coordinated network learning events such as the inaugural Innovations in International Philanthropy Symposium.', 'Managed grant-giving processes by initiating outreach, evaluating letters of intent, and conducting due diligence.', 6, 119),
(183, 'Democracy Facilitator (Volunteer)', 'Led civic education workshops for secondary school students in Boston to promote participation and civil rights.', 'Facilitated a student-lead advocacy project aiming to improve lunch quality by supporting students to develop campaign strategy, messaging, and outreach.', 6, 120),
(184, 'Co-Leader (Volunteer)', 'Organised volunteer opportunities for students to aid recently resettled refugees in the greater Boston area.', 'Initiated advocacy campaign to raise awareness of refugee issues in the Boston area.', 6, 121),
(185, 'Director of Programs & Operations', 'Managed programs and operations for a management, research and development firm providing global expertise for improved community resilience and self-reliance.', 'Managed numerous underperforming projects back on track. Ensured collective decision-making, capacity building, and care to multi-cultural teams across the UK, Europe and SSA. Included specific projects like USAID Ingobyi Project Endline Evaluation, USAID Inclusive Nutrition & Early Children Development Activity, Theory of Change co-design, MSC and Process Tracing Study, GIS Mapping Project, USAID Homes and Communities Activity, BMGF Ethnographic research study, Global Safeguarding Lead, and Business Development.', 7, 122),
(186, 'Co-Founder & Co-Director', 'Co-founded and co-directed a feminist consultancy firm supporting social change.', 'Included Public Engagement and Participation Advisor for the Malawi Epidemiology and Intervention Research Unit (MEIRU).', 7, 123),
(187, 'Senior Consultant: SRHR, Gender and Youth Participation focus', 'Provided senior consultancy with a focus on SRHR, Gender, and Youth Participation for One South LLC.', 'Included Baseline Evaluation of a SRHR AGYW-focused multi-agency project: Malawi, for Farm Radio International & CODE Canada. Endline Evaluation of a 5-year gender-responsive play-based learning project: Ghana, Mozambique & Rwanda, for Right to Play UK. Co-design, with young people, of a Theory of Change for a gender-transformative youth programme: global, IPPF (including proposal writing).', 7, 124),
(188, 'Consultant: SRHR, Gender and Youth Participation focus', 'Provided consultancy services for One South LLC.', 'Included Research Advisor: UNESCO Review of Comprehensive Sexuality Education in Malawi; Mixed Methods External Evaluation team: 4-country HelpAge International programme; Qualitative External Evaluation team: Right to Play Rwanda, Uganda and Mozambique. Situational Analysis of Comprehensive Sexuality Education in Secondary Schools & Universities, UNESCO Malawi. Gender Analysis: multi-country women\'s empowerment programme, DOT. Endline Evaluation using Process Tracing: Quantitative data analysis lead and final report writing, multi-country social protection programme, HelpAge. Quantitative and qualitative tool creation e.g. for a gender-responsive play-based programme, Right to Play.', 7, 125),
(189, 'Head of Education', 'Managed six projects focused on behaviour change, SRHR, and gender, improving coordination of implementation and learning.', 'Programme management portfolio: seven projects across Malawi - SRHR education, advocacy, gender equality, GBV and child protection government, traditional and school authorities; teachers & students; OVC; out-of-school girls; wider communities and community groups. TfaC Organisational Lead: Chair of National Girls\' Education Network creation of a School Child Protection Policy working group: Ministries of Education, Gender, and Justice; Malawi Police; Human Rights Commission co-creation of a network advocacy plan, leading to policy work, creation and national dissemination of advocacy materials, and network branding.', 7, 126),
(190, 'Girls Education Challenge Project Manager', 'Managed a DfID-funded 3-year project focusing on improving the life chances of marginalised girls in Central and Southern Malawi.', 'Co-created PIP, log frame and MEL framework; hit milestones & targets. Wrote SRH, gender equality, child protection and facilitation manuals. Designed and managed the accreditation of 2 OCN courses for teachers. Trained 350 female teachers to work in rural and peri-urban areas across 10 Districts working with targeted marginalised girls in schools and the community, parents and community leaders, as well as training other teachers in Child Protection and Gender-Inclusive Learning Environments.', 7, 127),
(191, 'HEM Academic Coordinator/Lead Academic Tutor', 'Supported the running of the Diploma in Liberal Studies course in Dzaleka Refugee Camp, Malawi. Integrated community service into the programme and ran regular and varied capacity building workshops for the Diploma students and other refugees.', 'Management of an online 3-year Diploma and associated teams. Support to student-led community outreach programme.', 7, 128),
(192, 'HIV360 Programme Manager and Acting Deputy CEO', 'Managed an EC-funded project involving participatory team project planning, full financial management, monitoring and evaluation, managing EC and partner relationships, and personnel management.', 'Full financial management including budgeting, forecasting, tracking, reporting. Monitoring and evaluation: regular internal and overseeing external. Managing EC and partner relationships including full narrative and financial reports to funders. Personnel management of 2 FT, 1 PT paid staff. Support to the Fundraising Team writing proposals. Child Protection duties as the organisation\'s Child Protection Assistant. SMT duties as the organisation\'s Acting Deputy CEO.', 7, 129),
(193, 'Youth Engagement and Participation Officer', 'Managed dance4life Youth Action and Peer Education areas, including planning, communications, budgeting, reporting, and monitoring and evaluation.', 'Part of the Management Committee for the Global Student Forum partnership and identified and developed other partnerships to increase youth engagement. Ensured good school/youth group-project relations. Developed all HIV educational materials. Recruited, trained, supported and managed 18-25 year old Peer Educators and project interns. Managed 2 weeks of the project\'s National Tour.', 7, 130),
(194, 'Research Officer & BeeBooks Creator and Manager (voluntary)', 'Designed and ran a consultation of 100 township households on under-5 and maternal healthcare. Initiated a communication network. Proposed and managed the creation of BeeBooks - a new social enterprise.', 'Recruited and trained 2 young local staff. Pushed for and coordinated Red Cross training for the organisations first 8 First Aiders. Managed the charity\'s \'Volunteer Village\'. Ran English Corners at the local school.', 7, 131),
(195, 'Adolescent Health Project Support', 'Facilitated and presented at promotional and educational workshops throughout the UK. Organised all meetings and events, including the project launch by Rt Hon Alan Johnson MP.', 'Ran communications with a multi-disciplinary group of stakeholders including young people. Monitored all finances and payments for this and another project. All admin duties: databases, agendas/minutes etc. Designed and disseminated publicity materials.', 7, 132),
(196, 'National Year of Reading 2008 Coordinator and PA to Director', 'Organised all project events and meetings including those with the funder.', 'All project administration including communications with stakeholders. Coordinated project team recruitment applications, interview schedules, feedback.', 7, 133),
(197, 'English Teacher', 'Taught English using a wide range of communication styles to suit learning types including individual adults, classes of 60 intermediate pupils, and primary school beginners.', 'Created syllabus for 1200 pupils involving games, dialogues and listening exercises including topics from fashion and music to divorce and the death penalty. Ran assessments for all students.', 7, 134),
(198, 'Alumni Mentor (Volunteer)', 'Provided mentorship to MSc in Public Health students at LSHTM.', NULL, 7, 135),
(199, 'Advocacy and Coordination Support (Volunteer)', 'Provided advocacy and coordination support to the Malawi movement for safe abortion.', NULL, 7, 136),
(200, 'Business Development Support and a Voice of Lived Experience (Volunteer)', 'Provided business development support and a voice of lived experience for the African Alliance for Maternal Mental Health.', NULL, 7, 137),
(201, 'Support to Various Groups (Volunteer)', 'Provided support to various groups including Girl Up (gender equity: secondary students), HIV Action Group (youth-led), and Teenage Parents Programme, UK.', NULL, 7, 138),
(202, 'Children\'s Centre Research Officer / BeeBooks Social Enterprise Founder & Manager (Volunteer)', 'Designed and ran 100-household consultation on under-5 and maternal healthcare. Proposed and created community book exchange, BeeBooks Social Enterprise Founder & Manager.', NULL, 7, 139),
(203, 'Editor and Transcriber (Volunteer)', 'Provided editing and transcription services for the UK AIDS and Human Rights Project.', NULL, 7, 140),
