(4, 'Emily Goldstein Consultancy', 'Accomplished monitoring, evaluation, and learning advisor specializing in gender and social inclusion.', 2016, 'emilysarahgoldstein@gmail.com', NULL, '+447769302607', 'Washington, District of Columbia, United States', 'To drive impactful social change through rigorous research, effective communication, and strategic advocacy.', 'To synthesize diverse, complex data into coherent narratives and actionable recommendations, empowering organizations to achieve greater social impact.', 'Expert in quantitative and qualitative analysis, transforming raw data into concrete results. Proven track record of delivering high-quality results in demanding environments, navigating across continents, cultures, and languages.', '[\"Monitoring, Evaluation, and Learning (MEL)\", \"Advocacy\", \"Communications\", \"Policy Analysis\", \"Fundraising\", \"Project Management\"]', '[\"Gender and Social Inclusion\", \"Private Sector Development\", \"Program Evaluations\", \"Data Synthesis\", \"Quantitative Analysis\", \"Qualitative Analysis\", \"Intercultural Communications\"]', '[\"Impact Evaluation\", \"Critical Discourse Analysis\", \"Advocacy Campaign Development\", \"Grant Management\", \"Community Mobilization\"]', '{\"years_experience\": 8, \"countries_worked_in\": [\"Latin America\", \"Europe\", \"U.S.\", \"India\", \"Kenya\", \"Malawi\"]}', '[\"Education\", \"Human Rights\", \"Humanitarian Action\", \"Child Protection\", \"Refugee Support\", \"Philanthropy\", \"Civic Engagement\"]', '[\"Inter-American Development Bank\", \"FCDO\", \"Global Affairs Canada\", \"IKEA Foundation\", \"UN\", \"US State Department\", \"French Embassy\", \"Nobel Peace Prize Laureate Nadia Murad\", \"ChildFund Alliance\", \"EQUITAS\", \"Girls Not Brides\", \"International AIDS Society (IAS)\", \"UNESCO\", \"Farm Radio International\", \"Girl Effect\", \"WCF\", \"HelpAge International\", \"Plan UK\", \"Sightsavers\", \"Abt Associates\", \"Transform Health\", \"Youth Business International\", \"Cherie Blair Foundation\", \"Save the Children\", \"Amnesty International\"]', '[\"Latin America\", \"Europe\", \"U.S.\", \"India\", \"Kenya\", \"Malawi\", \"Middle East\", \"East Africa\", \"Bangladesh\", \"Ghana\", \"Rwanda\", \"Mozambique\", \"Tanzania\", \"Uganda\", \"Cambodia\", \"Lao PDR\", \"Zambia\", \"South Africa\", \"Ireland\", \"Ethiopia\", \"Indonesia\", \"Ecuador\"]', 'Emily Goldstein Consultancy is committed to delivering high-quality, evidence-based solutions through rigorous analytical processes and clear communication. Quality assurance is integrated into every stage of project delivery.', 'Upholds the highest ethical standards in all research and advocacy, ensuring data privacy, informed consent, and respectful engagement with all stakeholders, particularly vulnerable populations.', 'Focuses on building sustainable capacities and fostering local ownership, ensuring that interventions are adaptable and continue to generate positive impact beyond the project lifecycle.'),
(5, 'Jo Seth-Smith Consultancy', 'Feminist | Gender Equity & SRHR | Consultant | Health, Rights and Power', 2001, 'joannasethsmith@gmail.com', 'www.linkedin.com/in/josethsmith', '+265997619209', 'Lilongwe, Central Region, Malawi, Malawi', 'A world where all groups, especially those marginalized by structural inequality, achieve health, rights, and power.', 'To improve the health, rights, and power of marginalized groups through feminist-informed consultancy, focusing on gender equity, sexual and reproductive health (SRH), young people, and youth participation.', 'Jo works with a strong focus on gender equity, SRHR, young people, and youth participation. She employs feminist leadership, builds strong relationships, drives innovative action, and champions youth voices in decision-making. Her approach emphasizes collective decision-making, capacity building, and care for multicultural teams.', '[\"Programme Management\", \"Organisational Support\", \"Feminist Consultancy\", \"SRHR Program Design\", \"Gender Equality\", \"Youth Participation\", \"Action Research\", \"Social Inclusion\", \"Monitoring, Evaluation & Learning (MEL)\"]', '[\"Gender Equity\", \"Sexual and Reproductive Health and Rights (SRHR)\", \"Youth Participation\", \"Feminist Leadership\", \"Social Inclusion\", \"Action Research\", \"Relationship Building\", \"Innovative Action\"]', '[\"Mixed Methods\", \"Impact Evaluation\", \"Process Tracing\", \"Contribution Analysis\", \"Outcome Harvesting\", \"Case Study Methodologies\", \"Longitudinal Study\", \"Participatory Evaluation\", \"Qualitative Thematic Analysis\", \"Theory of Change Development\"]', '{\"years_experience\": 13, \"countries_worked_in\": [\"Malawi\", \"UK\", \"Europe\", \"SSA\", \"Rwanda\", \"Uganda\", \"Mozambique\", \"Ghana\", \"China\"]}', '[\"Health\", \"Education\", \"Gender Equality\", \"Sexual and Reproductive Health and Rights (SRHR)\", \"Youth Development\", \"Child Protection\", \"Humanitarian Aid\", \"Literacy\", \"HIV/AIDS\", \"Social Protection\"]', '[\"USAID\", \"UN Women\", \"UNESCO\", \"DfID/FCDO\", \"European Commission (EC)\", \"Global Affairs Canada\", \"HelpAge International\", \"Right to Play\", \"IPPF\", \"DOT\", \"Farm Radio International\", \"CODE Canada\", \"Plan International\", \"Sightsavers\", \"Abt Associates\", \"Transform Health\", \"Youth Business International\", \"Cherie Blair Foundation\", \"Save the Children\", \"Amnesty International\", \"GIZ\", \"Medicor Foundation\", \"Comic Relief\", \"UN\", \"Wellcome Connecting Science\"]', '[\"Malawi\", \"UK\", \"Europe\", \"Sub-Saharan Africa (SSA)\", \"Rwanda\", \"Uganda\", \"Mozambique\", \"Ghana\", \"China\", \"Cambodia\", \"Laos PDR\", \"Tanzania\", \"Ireland\", \"South Africa\", \"Ethiopia\", \"Kenya\", \"India\", \"Honduras\", \"Paraguay\", \"Egypt\", \"Brazil\", \"Germany\", \"USA\"]', 'Jo Seth-Smith Consultancy ensures high-quality deliverables through a commitment to collective decision-making, rigorous research, and continuous learning. All projects are managed with meticulous attention to detail and adherence to ethical guidelines.', 'Jo has zero tolerance for negative discrimination based on sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, skin colour, cultural background, or seen or unseen disability including HIV status or mental health. All work is conducted with respect, inclusivity, and a strong ethical framework.', 'Committed to building sustainable social change through capacity building, empowering local partners, and fostering long-term resilience within communities. Solutions are designed to be adaptable and locally owned.'),
(6, 'Álvaro Bié Consultancy', 'Community Liaison and Participation Specialist | Social Behaviour Change Design', 2002, 'alvaro.bie@consultancy.com', NULL, NULL, 'Mozambique', 'To foster sustainable community-based development through effective engagement and social science research.', 'To provide expert consultancy in community liaison, social behavior change, and participatory research, driving positive outcomes in health, education, and social inclusion across Mozambique and the region.', 'Expert in Community engagement in Health and Development projects. Main interest areas include education, health, gender, social inclusion, WASH and resettlement. Brings deep expertise in quantitative and qualitative research, fieldwork management, and ethical research with human beings.', '[\"Community Liaison/Participation\", \"Social Behaviour Change Design\", \"Social and Environmental Safeguards\", \"Child Safeguarding\", \"Gender responsiveness\", \"Gender-Based Violence\", \"Community-based development projects Monitoring, Evaluation & Learning\", \"Quantitative Research\", \"Qualitative Research\", \"Quality Assurance\", \"Fieldwork Management\", \"Ethics and Research with Human Beings\"]', '[\"Community Engagement\", \"Social Behaviour Change\", \"Social Safeguards\", \"Child Protection\", \"Gender\", \"Monitoring, Evaluation & Learning (MEL)\", \"Research\"]', '[\"FGD\", \"KII\", \"Community Scorecard/Participatory Research\", \"SPSS\", \"NVivo\", \"Vignette approach\", \"Cross-sectional mixed methods study\"]', '{\"years_experience\": 15, \"countries_worked_in\": [\"Mozambique\"]}', '[\"Education\", \"Health\", \"Gender\", \"Social Inclusion\", \"WASH\", \"Resettlement\", \"Infrastructure\", \"Child Development\", \"Civil Registration\", \"Mining\", \"Human Rights\", \"HIV\"]', '[\"European Union (EU)\", \"Government of Mozambique - ANE\", \"Unicef\", \"Save The Children\", \"Right to Play Mozambique (RTP)\", \"Global Affairs Canada\", \"Italian Agency for Cooperation and Development (AICS)\", \"Girl Not Brides\", \"WaterAid\", \"Ministry of Justice\", \"HIKONE Mozambique\", \"Rosa Luxemburg\", \"International Organization for Migration (IOM)\", \"FH1360\", \"US Military HIV Research Program (MHRP)\"]', '[\"Mozambique\"]', 'Álvaro Bié Consultancy ensures quality through rigorous research design, ethical data collection, and robust analysis, delivering actionable insights for development projects. Adheres to Good Participation Practices (GPP).', 'Committed to ethical research and engagement, particularly in sensitive areas like child safeguarding, social and environmental safeguards, and gender-based violence. Ensures informed consent and community participation.', 'Focuses on building sustainable community capacity and fostering local ownership, ensuring project interventions are culturally sensitive and lead to long-term positive change.'),
(7, 'Paradious Sakala Consultancy', 'Serving the community with diligence, dedication to duty, honesty, discipline, humility and respect for humanity.', 1995, 'zuesakala@gmail.com', NULL, '+260977-434462', 'C/O P.O Box 50876, LUSAKA, Zambia', 'A productive and just society where all individuals, regardless of social status, contribute effectively.', 'To provide expert consultancy in organisational development, project management, disability rights advocacy, and community-based initiatives, fostering peace, leadership, and conflict resolution.', 'Paradious Sakala brings extensive experience in community social counseling, conflict management, strategic management planning, and project design from start to end. He is multi-skilled, adaptable, and capable of motivating staff and managing change.', '[\"Organisation Development\", \"Resource Mobilisation\", \"Strategic Planning\", \"Project Management\", \"Disability Rights Advocacy\", \"Capacity Building\", \"Policy Development\", \"Conflict Management\", \"Public Relations\", \"Journalism\"]', '[\"Disability Rights\", \"Community Development\", \"Conflict Resolution\", \"Organisational Development\", \"Public Administration\", \"Social Cash Transfer\"]', '[\"Social Research\", \"Qualitative Descriptive Research Design\", \"Arbitration (Conflict Resolution)\", \"Wealth Ranking Approaches\", \"Traditional Dispute Resolutions\"]', '{\"years_experience\": 29, \"countries_worked_in\": [\"Zambia\", \"Zimbabwe\", \"India\"]}', '[\"Disability\", \"Human Rights\", \"Education\", \"Social Protection\", \"Community Development\", \"Governance\", \"Health\", \"Journalism\"]', '[\"EU\", \"IRISH Aid\", \"FIDIDA\", \"Finnish Embassy\", \"Irish Embassy\", \"ZNAN\", \"ILO\", \"ADD\", \"DFID\", \"German Embassy\", \"NORAD\", \"AIR\", \"USAID\", \"World Bank\", \"European Commission for Humanitarian Aid Organization (ECHO)\", \"German Federal Ministry for Economic Cooperation and Development (BMZ)\", \"Churches\", \"Private Individuals\"]', '[\"Zambia\", \"Southern Africa\", \"India\"]', 'Paradious Sakala Consultancy is committed to delivering high-quality, impactful results through diligent project implementation, transparent reporting, and effective stakeholder coordination. Emphasizes accountability and continuous knowledge sharing.', 'Upholds principles of honesty, discipline, humility, and respect for humanity. Advocates for human rights, particularly disability rights, ensuring inclusivity and equitable treatment in all interventions.', 'Focuses on building sustainable community structures and empowering local leadership. Aims to design and implement programs that foster long-term self-reliance rather than charity-based approaches.'),
(8, 'Joel K. Maina Consultancy', 'Agricultural Economist / Financial & Economic Analyst / M&E Expert', 1995, 'joel.maina@example.com', NULL, NULL, 'Kenya', 'To drive sustainable economic development through expert agricultural, financial, and M&E analysis.', 'To provide high-quality technical assistance in project development, economic and financial analysis, and monitoring & evaluation for agricultural and infrastructure projects globally.', 'Joel K. Maina brings extensive experience in economic and financial analysis, project costing, investment planning, and M&E support. He excels in technical analysis, greenhouse gas accounting, and capacity building for various stakeholders across diverse sectors and geographies.', '[\"Economic Analysis\", \"Financial Analysis\", \"Monitoring & Evaluation (M&E)\", \"Project Development\", \"Project Costing\", \"Investment Planning\", \"Feasibility Studies\", \"Business Planning\", \"Strategic Planning\", \"Capacity Building\", \"Market Studies\", \"Policy Analysis\", \"Impact Assessment\", \"GHG Accounting\"]', '[\"Agricultural Economics\", \"Financial Modeling\", \"Infrastructure Development\", \"Climate Resilience\", \"Poverty Reduction\", \"Forced Displacement\", \"Water & Sanitation\", \"Irrigation\", \"Rural Development\", \"Value Chain Analysis\", \"Public-Private Partnerships (PPP)\"]', '[\"Baselines\", \"Midlines\", \"Impact Assessments\", \"Cost-Benefit Analysis (CBA)\", \"Financial Modeling\", \"Stakeholder Consultation\", \"Data Collection & Analysis\", \"Survey Design\", \"Economic Impact Assessments\"]', '{\"years_experience\": 29, \"countries_worked_in\": [\"Kenya\", \"Rwanda\", \"Tanzania\", \"Uganda\", \"Burundi\", \"DRC\", \"Zimbabwe\", \"Malawi\", \"Zambia\", \"Mozambique\", \"Seychelles\", \"Comoros\", \"Liberia\", \"Nigeria\", \"Ethiopia\", \"Somalia\", \"South Sudan\"]}', '[\"Agriculture\", \"Water & Sanitation\", \"Poverty\", \"Forced Displacement\", \"Climate Change\", \"Infrastructure\", \"Energy\", \"Livelihoods\", \"Food Security\", \"Trade\", \"Environment\"]', '[\"World Bank Group\", \"GIZ\", \"Ministry of Water Sanitation and Irrigation (MOWSI)\", \"National Irrigation Authority\", \"NGCDF\", \"AfDB\", \"USAID\", \"FAO\", \"Kenya Pipeline Corporation\", \"United States African Development Foundation (USADF)\", \"Athi Water Services Board\", \"Lake Victoria South Water Services Board\", \"TANATHI Water Services Board\", \"Ministry of Regional Development\", \"SME International\", \"National Irrigation Board (NIB)\", \"Swisscontact East Africa\", \"Ford Foundation\", \"Royal Tropical Institute\", \"Gatsby Foundation\", \"ICIPE\", \"World Food Programme (WFP)\", \"Child Fund\", \"Baker Tilley Merallis\", \"Privatization Commission\", \"PWC Kenya\", \"Financial Sector Deepening (FSD Kenya)\", \"African Agricultural Technology Foundation (AATF)\", \"ICRISAT\", \"Society for Family Health (SFH)\", \"Kenya Markets Trust (KMT)\", \"National Information Platform For Food Security And Nutrition Project (NIPFN)\", \"MESPT\", \"DANIDA\", \"Equity Group Foundation\", \"NORAD\", \"AGRA\", \"Ministry Of Environment, Climate Change And Forestry\", \"Safer World Kenya\", \"Hand-in Hand Eastern Africa\", \"Practical Action\", \"IUCN\", \"PELUM Kenya\", \"Research Triangle Institute International (RTI)\", \"GAIN Nutrition (Switzerland)\"]', '[\"Kenya\", \"South Sudan\", \"Comoros\", \"Tanzania\", \"Rwanda\", \"Uganda\", \"Burundi\", \"DRC\", \"Zimbabwe\", \"Malawi\", \"Zambia\", \"Mozambique\", \"Seychelles\", \"Liberia\", \"Nigeria\", \"Ethiopia\", \"Somalia\"]', 'Joel K. Maina Consultancy is committed to delivering high-quality, evidence-based solutions through rigorous economic and financial analysis, robust M&E systems, and strategic planning. Ensures project viability and sustainable impact.', 'Upholds professional integrity and ethical standards in all engagements. Ensures transparency, accountability, and responsible use of data in all research and analysis.', 'Focuses on building sustainable capacities within organizations and communities, promoting local ownership, and fostering long-term resilience and economic growth through well-planned and evaluated interventions.');
