(63, 'Zambia Inclusive Education “Tusambilile Chapamo” (Let’s Learn Together) End of Term Evaluation', 'Sightsavers', '2024-10-01', '2025-04-30', 'Conducted an End of Term Evaluation (ETE) to assess the project\'s performance and derive essential insights for future programme development and execution. The evaluation examined the project\'s relevance, effectiveness, impact, sustainability, scalability, and equity and inclusion, with a specific focus on the low-cost inclusive education model\'s effectiveness and potential for replication. Utilized a mixed-methods approach with qualitative and quantitative data collection, including participatory methods.', '[\"Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning (MEAL)\", \"Inclusive Education\", \"Disability Inclusion\"]', '[\"Mixed-methods\", \"Qualitative Study\", \"Document Review\", \"Contribution Analysis\", \"Outcome Harvesting\", \"Most Significant Change\"]', 1),
(64, 'MEL Consultant – Local Health System Sustainability (LHSS) Project, East Africa', 'Abt Associates', '2025-01-01', '2025-05-31', 'Supported MEL implementation for cross-border HIV/AIDS and SRHR services across Kenya, Uganda, and Tanzania under the USAID-funded LHSS Project. Led data collection, analysis, learning facilitation, and reporting to strengthen regional collaboration, digital readiness, and evidence use. The project aims to improve financial protection, population coverage, and service delivery for essential health services.', '[\"HIV/AIDS\", \"Sexual and Reproductive Health and Rights (SRHR)\", \"Digital Health\", \"Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning (MEAL)\"]', '[\"Routine Health Information System (RHIS) Analysis\", \"Learning Facilitation\", \"Digital Readiness Assessment\"]', 1),
(65, 'Case Study Review for Transform Health National Coalitions (Kenya, Ecuador, Indonesia)', 'Transform Health', '2024-08-01', '2025-05-31', 'Conducted multi-country documentation of national coalition experiences and pathways toward digital health policy and legislation in Kenya, Ecuador, and Indonesia. The case study aimed to document the evolution, best practices, and advocacy strategies of Transform Health national coalitions, particularly their influence in shaping digital health policies.', '[\"Digital Health\", \"Health Systems\", \"Advocacy and Campaigns\", \"Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning (MEAL)\"]', '[\"Case Study Documentation\", \"Key Informant Interviews\", \"Document Review\", \"Qualitative Thematic Analysis\"]', 1),
(66, 'Endline Evaluation of the Accelerating Youth-led Businesses in the Digital Era', 'Youth Business International', '2022-10-01', '2022-11-30', 'Evaluated a multi-country programme supporting youth entrepreneurship in Bangladesh and India through digital skills and business mentorship. The programme aimed to empower youth entrepreneurs with decent work principles, business planning, and digital tools, also addressing gender and inclusion in access to finance, networks, and markets. The role involved leading evaluation design, managing remote field teams, developing tools, conducting qualitative and quantitative analysis, and applying contribution analysis and collaborative outcomes reporting.', '[\"Youth Economic Empowerment\", \"Youth Entrepreneurship\", \"Digital Skills Training\", \"Gender Equality and Social Inclusion (GESI)\", \"Decent Work and Employment\"]', '[\"Mixed-methods\", \"Collaborative Outcomes Reporting (COR)\", \"Contribution Analysis\"]', 1),
(67, 'Final Evaluation for Road to Growth Kenya', 'Cherie Blair Foundation', '2022-06-01', '2022-07-31', 'Evaluated the Road to Growth Kenya project, which supported women entrepreneurs. The project aimed to empower 3,500 women entrepreneurs with business skills, financial literacy, and leadership through digital tools like the HerVenture App, online training, and advocacy sessions, targeting small and medium-sized businesses in Kenya. The evaluation included design, secondary data analysis of baseline and endline data, facilitation of qualitative FGDs and KIIs, and synthesis of findings.', '[\"Financial Literacy\", \"Women’s Economic Empowerment\", \"Entrepreneurship\", \"Leadership Development\"]', '[\"Collaborative Outcomes Reporting (COR)\", \"Contribution Analysis\", \"Mixed-methods\"]', 1),
(68, 'Final Evaluation for Tuwekeze Pamoja Project', 'Save the Children', '2022-04-01', '2022-05-31', 'Conducted the final evaluation of an early childhood development project targeting caregivers, teachers, and communities in Songwe Region, Tanzania. The project aimed to improve Early Childhood Development (ECD) outcomes through parenting education, teacher training, school environment improvements, and community engagement, reaching over 30,000 children.', '[\"Early Childhood Development\", \"Gender Equality and Social Inclusion (GESI)\", \"Inclusive Education\", \"Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning (MEAL)\"]', '[\"Mixed-methods\", \"Theory-Based Evaluation\", \"Focus Group Discussions\", \"Key Informant Interviews\", \"Document Review\"]', 1),
(69, 'Strengthening Amnesty’s MEL System', 'Amnesty International', '2025-07-01', '2025-10-31', 'Supports Amnesty’s review of its global KPI metrics, focusing on improving KPI calculations, assessing relationships between different KPIs and/or other metrics, and enhancing data disaggregation and visualisation for improved interpretation and reporting. The assignment also includes designing and delivering a capacity-building plan for the core team on evaluation methods. The overall aim is to improve, simplify, and ensure the MEL system responds to key stakeholders\' needs.', '[\"Human Rights\", \"Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning (MEAL)\"]', '[\"KPI calculations\", \"Data analysis methods\", \"Data visualisation\", \"Capacity building\"]', 1),
(70, 'Consultancy Services at Ikocila Associates Ltd.', 'Multiple Clients (e.g., Save the Children, World Vision, UNDP)', '2021-07-01', NULL, 'Provided technical M&E leadership, proposal development, M&E training, and led various researches, assessments, surveys, baselines, evaluations, and impact assessments for diverse clients.', '[\"Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning (MEAL)\", \"Research\", \"Capacity Building\"]', '[\"Baselines\", \"Evaluations\", \"Assessments\", \"Surveys\", \"Impact Assessments\"]', 2),
(71, 'Regional M&E System Development and Reporting - WaterAid East Africa', 'WaterAid East Africa', '2016-12-01', '2021-03-31', 'Led the design of research and development of monitoring and evaluation systems for all countries (Uganda, Kenya, Tanzania, Rwanda, Ethiopia). Led M&E training for staff, managed regional planning, consolidated annual plans and reports, introduced learning initiatives, and developed user counting protocols.', '[\"Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning (MEAL)\", \"Capacity Building\", \"WASH\", \"Learning\"]', '[\"M&E System Design\", \"Reporting\", \"Training\", \"Strategic Planning\", \"Program Review\"]', 2),
